  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "- [x] üêõ This is a bug report.\r\n- [ ] üìà This is a feature request.\r\n\r\nFunction `mint` from MintableToken returns a boolean value, similar to `transfer`. However, its return value is not checked when the token is [used in the Crowdsale contract](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/zeppelin-solidity/blob/master/contracts/crowdsale/Crowdsale.sol#L78).\r\n\r\nInstead of:\r\n```\r\ntoken.mint(beneficiary, tokens);\r\n```\r\nShould be:\r\n```\r\nrequire(token.mint(beneficiary, tokens));\r\n```\r\n\r\nOn the other hand, the implementation of mint does not return false, and instead should revert if it fails. \r\n\r\nDiscuss whether we want to remove the return value from `mint`, or we want to check it whenever we invoke the method.",
